festival.introText:
BACK FOR OUR 3rd YEAR DUE TO MASSIVE SUCCESS.

Fife Fest will be a fantastic festival for families and the local community to enjoy a great weekend of music and entertainment from some of the Top Tribute Bands in the UK along with some of our own local talent.

The venue is unquestionably one of the best green spaces in Fife, taking over Silverburn Parks Festival Green. 2 big tents will be tree lined which makes for a great atmosphere. 

This is a family friendly event and outside the tents will be kids entertainment and also food trucks.

As part of licensing once festival goers are scanned in you will not be permitted to come

and go from the site.

There is a strict “zero tolerance” approach to any unfriendly or unsociable behaviour and we enforce a responsible drinking atmosphere.

No alcohol, food or drinks may be brought into the festival and bags will be searched upon entry.

Camping chairs are permitted but not inside of the tents.

reviews.title: Review of Fife Fest
reviews.body: I enjoyed the event, however the fact you could not leave then return made it very expensive. The alcohol was over priced as was the food. Not enough for children to do or space to play once everyone had their chairs up.

reviews.title: Review of Fife Fest
reviews.body: Bands were double acts, a little dissapointing to see two bands play as 4 cover bands.. People had fun and the day as a whole was fine although ended being an expensive one.

faqs.question: When is Fife Fest 2023?
faqs.answer: Fife Fest takes place Saturday 9th September - Sunday 10th September 2023.

faqs.question: How do you get to Fife Fest?
faqs.answer: Silverburn Park is located just off the A915 between Lundin Links and Leven en route to St Andrews.

faqs.question: How much are tickets for Fife Fest?
faqs.answer:
Adult day tickets start at just £33.00 + BF, weekend tickets are available for £50.50 + BF.

A youth ticket can be purchased alongside an adult ticket for £20+BF.

All children under 10 go free.

faqs.question: Where is Fife Fest?
faqs.answer: Fife Fest is located at Silverburn Park in Leven. The full address is Largo Rd, Lundin Links, Leven KY8 5PU.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately, we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: Does Fife Fest have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer:
Fife Fest is a family-friendly festival however, children (under 17) must be accompanied by an adult over 21.

They operate a strict Challenge 25 policy at the bar areas.

Entry to Fife Fest will only be permitted on production of a valid ticket or e-ticket. Proof of age may be requested for concession tickets.

Event Organisers reserve the right to refuse admission to ticket holders who arrive at the event drunk or who are behaving disorderly.

Fife Fest encourages a family feels to the festival and any anti-social behavior will not be tolerated and you will be asked to leave.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Fife Fest?
faqs.answer: Only food or drink purchased on site will be allowed to be consumed at the event. No food or drink can be brought on to the site and this will be enforced by searches at the entry point.
